[http://corega.jp/prod/wlbargs/ Product page (JP)] "8WRGG15C.2A1" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos. The device uses AR2315A, per the [http://www.dd-wrt.com/wiki/index.php/Supported_Devices DD-WRT wiki]. Per the Quick Install Guide, the SSID follows the format of '''Jumpstart-P1-XXXXXX'''. :The FCC manual notes the default SSID as '''corega'''. ==Probable used PSU(s)== The power supply shown in the FCC photos is a '''JENTEC''' JTA0302D. {{hasPowerSupply |brand=JENTEC |model=JTA0302D |input_v=100-240 |input_a=0.5 |input_c=AC |input_hz=50-60 |input_conn=NEMA 1-15P |output_v=5 |output_a=2 |output_c=DC |output_conn=barrel |manuf_country=China |style=small, straight }} __NOTOC__
